    #!/bin/bash
    <::before>
    # Compliance Audit Script
    # This script performs basic compliance checks on target servers
    <::before>
    echo "Starting compliance audit..."
    echo "Timestamp: $(date)"
    echo "----------------------------------------"
    <::before>
    # Target server information
    SERVER="172.22.100.44"
    USER="auditor"
    <::before>
    # Function to run remote commands
    run_remote_command() {
        echo "Running: $1"
        ssh $USER@$SERVER "$1"
        echo "----------------------------------------"
    }
    <::before>
    # Check system logs for errors
    echo "Checking system logs for errors..."
    run_remote_command "cd /var/log && grep -i 'error' syslog | tail -n 10"
    <::before>
    # Check disk usage
    echo "Checking disk usage..."
    run_remote_command "df -h"
    <::before>
    # Check for unauthorized users
    echo "Checking for unauthorized sudo access..."
    run_remote_command "grep -i 'sudo' /var/log/auth.log | tail -n 5"
    <::before>
    # Check for failed login attempts
    echo "Checking for failed login attempts..."
    run_remote_command "grep -i 'failed' /var/log/auth.log | tail -n 5"
    <::before>
    echo "Compliance audit completed."
    echo "Timestamp: $(date)"

This repository contains automated scripts for performing compliance audits on our server infrastructure. 

##  <::after> Purpose 

These scripts help automate the process of checking server configurations, logs, and security settings to ensure compliance with industry standards and internal policies. 

##  <::after> Features 

  * <::marker>Automated log analysis for error detection 
  * <::marker>Server configuration validation 
  * <::marker>Security compliance checks 
  * <::marker>Centralized reporting

To run a basic audit: 
    
    
    ./run_audit.sh

##  <::after> Requirements 

  * <::marker>SSH access to target servers 
  * <::marker>Appropriate permissions to read log files and system configurations

This repository contains scripts that connect to internal systems. Ensure proper credentials management and do not expose sensitive information in the scripts.

    #!/bin/bash
    <::before>
    # Compliance Audit Script
    # This script performs basic compliance checks on target servers
    <::before>
    echo "Starting compliance audit..."
    echo "Timestamp: $(date)"
    echo "----------------------------------------"
    <::before>
    # Target server information
    SERVER="172.22.100.44"
    USER="auditor"
    <::before>
    # Function to run remote commands
    run_remote_command() {
        echo "Running: $1"
        ssh $USER@$SERVER "$1"
        echo "----------------------------------------"
    }
    <::before>
    # Check system logs for errors
    echo "Checking system logs for errors..."
    run_remote_command "cd /var/log && grep -i 'error' syslog | tail -n 10"
    <::before>
    # Check disk usage
    echo "Checking disk usage..."
    run_remote_command "df -h"
    <::before>
    # Check for unauthorized users
    echo "Checking for unauthorized sudo access..."
    run_remote_command "grep -i 'sudo' /var/log/auth.log | tail -n 5"
    <::before>
    # Check for failed login attempts
    echo "Checking for failed login attempts..."
    run_remote_command "grep -i 'failed' /var/log/auth.log | tail -n 5"
    <::before>
    echo "Compliance audit completed."
    echo "Timestamp: $(date)"

        echo "----------------------------------------"
    }
    <::before>
    # Check system logs for errors
    echo "Checking system logs for errors..."
    run_remote_command "cd /var/log && grep -i 'error' syslog | tail -n 10"
    <::before>
    # Check disk usage
    echo "Checking disk usage..."
    run_remote_command "df -h"
    <::before>
    # Check for unauthorized users
    echo "Checking for unauthorized sudo access..."
    run_remote_command "grep -i 'sudo' /var/log/auth.log | tail -n 5"
    <::before>
    # Check for failed login attempts
    echo "Checking for failed login attempts..."
    run_remote_command "grep -i 'failed' /var/log/auth.log | tail -n 5"
    <::before>
    echo "Compliance audit completed."
